This function handles resuming a schedule by constructing a specialized request body. It uses the input `index` to locate a specific thermostat's identifier before sending the command.

```python
def resume_program(self, index, resume_all=False):
        ''' Resume currently scheduled program '''
        body = {"selection": {
                    "selectionType": "thermostats",
                    "selectionMatch": self.thermostats[index]['identifier']},
                "functions": [{"type": "resumeProgram", "params": {
                    "resumeAll": resume_all
                }}]}

        log_msg_action = "resume program"
        return self.make_request(body, log_msg_action)
```

The final call to `self.make_request` executes this defined action, allowing you to either target one device or resume all programs simultaneously via the boolean parameter.
